## Concordance with HGMD

> **What this measures — read before the numbers.** The gold set *is* HGMD's curated citation
> list, so these are scores of **concordance with HGMD, not coverage of the true literature**.
> Recall has a **hard ceiling at HGMD**: a correct paper HGMD did not list cannot raise it.
> Precision charges every retrieved paper *outside* HGMD's list (which is broad — primary
> **plus** additional **plus** extra references, not primary-only) as a false positive — and
> some of those may be correct papers HGMD simply omitted. So neither number alone answers
> "can we drop HGMD?"; they bound "how well does the free pipeline reproduce HGMD's bibliography."

