**Scored over {{ per_doc|length }} of {{ r.n_documents }} variant(s)** — {{ degraded|length }} with degraded/uncovered retrieval excluded (see Retrieval integrity below).

> **Macro vs micro (both shown, neither is "the" number).** Macro weights every variant
> equally, so it is dominated by the many single-citation variants; micro weights every gold
> PMID equally, so it better reflects "what share of all known citations did we find." When a
> dataset mixes easy single-paper variants with hard many-paper ones, the two diverge — compare
> them rather than reading one in isolation.

